The Netherlands’ Ministry of Foreign Affairs in partnership with the Issam Fares Institute for Public Policy and International Affairs at the American University of Beirut has been holding sub-regional policy dialogues on the Water – Energy – Food (WEF) Security Nexus for countries of the Levant as part of the Planetary Security Initiative Middle East and North Africa chapter activities. The policy dialogue brought together senior representatives from Ministries of Water, Energy and Agriculture from Iraq, Lebanon, Jordan and Palestine.

A team of Dutch experts, together with the NGO's NL Red Cross, Wetlands International and Cordaid, provided advice to the Philippine government on coastal protection and disaster risk reduction around the city of Tacloban.

In January 2015, Mozambique faced the worst floods on the Licungo river since 1971. DRR-Team was requested to support to the Government of Mozambique through deployment of the DRR-Team. Particular focus was on Technical Assistance to assist the National Directorate of Water  in the elaboration of inundations maps, to evaluate the state of the dikes protecting Nante and Marromeu in the Licungu basin and to assist DNA with the development of a  post flood plan for priority and strategic actions to respond to the flood affected area.
